# Code owners for review routing.
#
# Ownership follows the change's blast radius, not its file type: anything that
# can alter how the repository builds, ships, or is gated belongs to Platform
# Admins; product behaviour belongs to Product Engineering.
#
# Dependency manifests are deliberately NOT owned by Platform Admins. Product
# engineers change them constantly, and routing every bump through infra review
# is the friction that gets CODEOWNERS deleted. Dependency risk is already
# covered by pip-audit, npm audit, and Snyk.
#
# NOTE: a team must have write access to this repository for GitHub to honour
# it here. Without that, these lines are silently ignored.

# Default owner — product behaviour.
*                           @city-of-baltimore/product-engineering

# CI, containers, orchestration, and the platform baseline.
/.github/                   @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
/Dockerfile*                @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
/compose*.yml               @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
/compose*.yaml              @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
/docker-compose*.yml        @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
/nginx/                     @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
/Taskfile.yml               @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
/scripts/                   @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
/.pre-commit-config.yaml    @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
/.baltimore-lab-app.toml    @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
/fly.toml                   @city-of-baltimore/platform-admins
